LC001.001 - LC001.006:  Old and historic houses in East Lyme, Connecticut; 
LC001.001 - LC001.002:  Surveys of individual houses done by the WPA in 1930s also the State of Connecticut Historic Resources Inventory of building and structures in the 1970s. All arranged alphabetically by street name; 
LC001.003: Historic Resources Inventory  212 properties that are 125 years and older in the Town of East Lyme (compiled in 2013); 
LC001.004: Compilation of inventories and surveys of old houses in chronological order by the WPA, Connecticut Historical Commission and, Vision Quest;
LC001.005: Samuel Smith Farm Stead contains the history and preservation of the farm stead; 
LC001.006: Thomas Lee House - the history and preservation of the house compiled by the East Lyme Historical Society.

LC006.001:  General information about the various churches; 
LC006.002:  Records of thd 2nd Society of Lyme, 1719-1857;   
LC006.003: Records related to the Second Ecclesiastical Society of Lyme, which became the First Congregational Church of East Lyme, 1828-1912; 
LC006.004: Old Stone Church burial grounds, East Lyme: records and burial list, 1907-1951

LC007.001: Miscellaneous items pertaining to the history of Connecticut State Farm for Women, now known as York Correctional Institution;  
LC007.002:  Notebook of Connecticut State Farm Annual and Biennial Reports to the Governor, 191-1948, 1962-1970; 
LC007.003:  Newspaper articles from Janet S. York's personal collection, 1914-2005; 
LC007.004: Medical records, Reports, and Statistics, 1918-1944.

LC008.001:  Photos and postcards of Niantic National Guard Camp, 1887-1917;  
LC008.002:  Correspondence between Byran Clark and the Quartermaster General about the borders of the camp; 
LC008.003:  A Brief History of Stone's Ranch by Ford Hilton.
